The paper focuses on iris segmentation using deep learning techniques, specifically Fully Convolutional Networks (FCNs) and Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs). This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with biometric authentication, which could be categorized under multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also discusses the robustness of the segmentation techniques, which could be classified under cryptography and security (cs.CR).
